description: {"blocks":[{"key":"dcrl2","text":"This protocol describes nuclei extraction from snap frozen tissue (human or mouse) using Singulator, including washing nuclei suspension in buffer supplemented with sucrose, and nuclei FACS sorting. The resulting nuclei suspension is suitable for scRNA-seq using a platform of choice (as 10X Chromium, or inDrops). The protocol has been validated on various snap frozen human and mouse tissues (lung, brain, prostate, tumors, core needle biopsies amongst others).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

fork_info.title: Nuclei extraction for  single-cell RNAseq from frozen tissue using Singulator™ 100 (Citric Acid preservation)

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"erkqk","text":"Add RNAse inhibitor (0.2-1.0 U/uL final depending on tissue type - Final volume ~ 3.5 mL for standard protocol, ~2.5 for low volume) and DTT (1M, final 1mM) directly into Nuclei Isolation Cartridge just before the run.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4cc2d","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"tlt6","text":"Transfer tissue into the cooled Nuclei Isolation Cartridge and start Nuclei isolation protocol. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"efml7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"379r5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1r38u","text":"When run is over on Singulator, transfer nuclei suspension (~3.5mL for standard protocol) into two 2 mL Protein LoBind Tubes (Eppendorf, 0030108450) (split evenly, ~1750 uL each).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":137,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":137,"length":10}],"data":{}},{"key":"2cs4t","text":"1.5mL Protein LoBind Tubes (Eppendorf) can be used for low yield samples i.e. biopsies and/or low volume protocol.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"1AD3345C44A911ECB1660A58A9FEAC02","url":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bemtn","text":"Add 250uL of   Sucrose solution to both tubes ( final).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":13,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":47,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"2j8pq","text":"Invert the tube slowly 10 times to mix sucrose and nuclei suspension.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"concentration","mutability":"","data":{"concentration":"2","error_concentration":false,"guid":"2164BC8444A911ECB1660A58A9FEAC02","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":21}},"1":{"type":"concentration","mutability":"","data":{"concentration":"250","error_concentration":false,"guid":"2164BDBC44A911ECB1660A58A9FEAC02","id":0,"label":"","scientificNotation":false,"unit":28}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"chk6c","text":"After centrifugation, a layer of debris might be visible at the top and a pellet of nuclei at the bottom (for lower yields it might not be noticeable). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"67g08","text":"Aspirate supernatant with a P1000 pipette, be really careful when removing the debris layer on the meniscus without disrupting nuclei pellet at the bottom of the tube (some liquid can be left to prevent pellet aspiration ~50uL). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1n372","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"15bn7","text":"Resuspend Nuclei pellet in 250uL Nuclei Wash Buffer, then using same pipette tip transfer this nuclei suspension to other tubes pooling all tubes together.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5eol8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
